.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-HOSTS 5 "2026-04-20" "shorewall-nft 1.10.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-hosts \- host/subnet zone membership for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I hosts
file assigns specific hosts or subnets on an interface to a zone.  Use it
when a single physical interface carries traffic from multiple zones and you
cannot use VLAN tagging or separate interfaces.

The compiler emits dispatch rules that match both
.B iifname
and source/destination address against the host list.  Entries here take
precedence over the zone-level assignment in
.IR interfaces .

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/hosts
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
ZONE	yes	Zone name (must be in zones file)
HOSTS	yes	interface:address[,address…] list
OPTIONS	no	Comma-separated options (ipsec, nosmurfs, …)
.TE

.I HOSTS
format:
.IB interface : address
where
.I address
is a CIDR prefix, a single IP, or
.B !address
for negation.

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Assign two subnets on the same interface to different zones:
.RS
.nf
#ZONE    HOSTS
loc      eth1:192.168.1.0/24
mgmt     eth1:10.0.99.0/24
.fi
.RE
.PP
IPv6 zone on a shared interface:
.RS
.nf
loc      eth1:192.168.1.0/24
loc6     eth1:fd00::/64
.fi
.RE
.PP
IPSEC zone restricted to a VPN peer:
.RS
.nf
vpn      eth0:203.0.113.5
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-zones (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-interfaces (5)

